parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Delamination and Liner Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the fuel tank liner can cause fuel system damage, engine stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

The failure of fuel system components, such as fuel injectors, fuel pumps, and fuel filters, can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and rough engine idle, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving on highways or in heavy traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: 6.0L Diesel Engine Power Issues and Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and power issues can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle loses power while driving, and can lead to safety risks on the public highway.

The failure of the fuel tank coating can cause the fuel tank to peel apart, clog the fuel filter, and lead to engine stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to restart
the fuel filter is clogged with debris from the fuel tank coating.
